# Design + build routine

## Kid-friendly color principles
- Background: warm off-white `#F7F6F5`; surfaces `#FFFFFF`.
- Text: navy `#002559` (never light gray on white).
- Default accent: calm blue `#244CB3`; supporting teal `#77C0D9`, green `#6CD97E`, amber `#FFCA61`.
- Red `#FA4033` only for errors — not for buttons or large fields.
- Per-kid hero accents (override `--c-primary`):
  - Ishanvi: warm amber/orange `#D97706`
  - Aadya: pink/magenta `#E84C8A`
- Headings: IBM Plex Serif. Body/UI: Inter. Telugu: Noto Sans Telugu.
- Flat, clean style — avoid heavy purple gradients and neon shadows.

## Build routine (every change)
After implementing any feature or fix:
1. Run `npm run build` to verify TypeScript + Vite build passes.
2. Run `npm run cap:apk` to produce a fresh debug APK (`android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`).
3. Commit all changes and push to GitHub.

Add "build APK" and "push to GitHub" as explicit todos in every session that changes code.
